preLoad

void preLoad(E eventBus,
             java.lang.String eventName,
             java.lang.Object[] params,
             com.google.gwt.user.client.Command load)
Called before a module/code splitter is loaded. To start the code loading, the load command must be executed. This way, asynchronous action can be made.

Parameters:
eventBus - The event bus loading the code (ie in case of child module, the parent event bus).
eventName - The name of the event that requested the module to be loaded, null if the request come from a history token change.
params - The objects fired with this event, null is no object are fired with the event or if the request come from a history token change.
load - The command to execute when the module needs to be loaded.

onFailure

void onFailure(E eventBus,
               java.lang.String eventName,

Called if the module/code splitter couldn't be loaded.

Parameters:
eventBus - The event bus loading the code (ie in case of child module, the parent event bus).
eventName - The name of the event that requested the module to be loaded, null if the request come from a history token change.
params - The objects fired with this event, null is no object are fired with the event or if the request come from a history token change.
err - The error thrown.
